>>80329656-4307-42da-ac62-0e62207f53fc
Also should I even bother keeping those tiny little squad guys, they're annoying to fight but I can't help but feel like they're less useful in my hands then the AI's.

>>73ca722b-6dbb-4812-bdb0-df27191f5534
Honestly you should be more concerned with the guys who have seedboxes setup to download everything at once, then the groups of anons you'll end up being permanently attached to from use of the Mute function. Which is how the Fed will be doing it too.

>>67107dc8-1cce-4474-9064-f9f47d80e399
>Effectively they're the "bump" and "sage," or "upvote" and "downvote," respectively. 
OP managed to prove everyone who said sage wasn't a downvote wrong in one sentence. Putting that aside Mute is too much of a hassle to get rid to deal with on a regular basis unless Acidman decides to put in an unmute function, so it is a lot more semi-permanent then a simple downvote.

>>b24efb34-fa0a-4ca3-a05a-1ab8f16f3b2a
Might as well ask now, but what is the most convenient way to unMute someone? I accidentally hit it when looking up an ID and I don't want to scrub the whole list for one guy.

EDIT: Nevermind I'm retarded.

>>516e0443-12e6-4cce-810e-e0aa2e47cfb7
Not knowing who made this pretty much says everything about how small crossboarding between /v/ and /pol/ is. The maker is Acidman, if you wanna know who that is he is a gun store owner in the US with friends in the FBI. I know this because some discord group tried to dox and raid him but he asked his friend to take care of them.

>>98fa0a82-3ff7-438e-b77a-5f60bab46826
You could always set your ship to autopilot, but there is some stuff the AI does which is kind of dumb. Just got to get used to it.
